<span id="freeTextContainer11102253782099898872">This book is sort of two things, a story of unconsummated love between Rita and Israel and a look at the pre-WW2 world, particularly Cuba and Paris, through the eyes of a musician. The third leg of it, if you will, is mentions of Israel&apos;s magnificent virility. I read a review after the fact that mentioned the book lacked a strong narrative thread, and that&apos;s definitely the case. The bulk of it is adequate, but it doesn&apos;t sing. The ending is better, but it wasn&apos;t enough to lift this to 4, I think</span>
  <span id="freeText11102253782099898872" style="display:none">This book is sort of two things, a story of unconsummated love between Rita and Israel and a look at the pre-WW2 world, particularly Cuba and Paris, through the eyes of a musician. The third leg of it, if you will, is mentions of Israel's magnificent virility. I read a review after the fact that mentioned the book lacked a strong narrative thread, and that's definitely the case. The bulk of it is adequate, but it doesn't sing. The ending is better, but it wasn't enough to lift this to 4, I think.</span>
